Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.95,0:00:23.29,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right! Now let's move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.29,0:00:26.92,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with the sun always in our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.92,0:00:30.09,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,As power passes through our clasped hands
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.09,0:00:33.67,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,let's grab hold of our wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.27,0:00:48.77,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Working together, let's ride the giant waves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.77,0:00:55.99,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry toward the excitement--\Nthere's the starting signal
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.99,0:01:02.95,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Now's the time to set sail-- let's raise anchor
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.95,0:01:10.09,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut through the rainbow-colored wind\Nand head for a sea of adventure
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.09,0:01:13.55,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a journey fraught with injury
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.55,0:01:17.43,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,but what you cherish most will be right there
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.43,0:01:21.43,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you get into a jam
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.43,0:01:24.48,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll always be there to protect you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.48,0:01:28.65,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right! Now let's move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.65,0:01:32.19,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with the sun always in our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.19,0:01:35.19,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If a storm hits, let's put\Nour arms around each other
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.19,0:01:39.70,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and gaze at the light beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.70,0:01:43.41,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If we gather up the pieces of our dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.41,0:01:46.71,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,they'll make a map leading to tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.71,0:01:49.67,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's grab hold of our wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.67,0:01:55.46,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,under the same flag-- together, we're one
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.46,0:01:58.09,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,One Piece
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.94,0:02:14.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A frog is doing the front crawl!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.40,0:02:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.40,0:02:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It went to your side, so take a look at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.44,0:02:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Is that true?\N--Hey, Luffy...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.20,0:02:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you taking what that\Nstupid Admiral said seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.49,0:02:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To start with, there's no way a frog\Nwould do the front cra... Hey, it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.58,0:02:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A frog is doing the front crawl!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.08,0:02:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll follow it, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.25,0:02:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.42,0:02:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is there a lighthouse in a place\Nlike that? I wonder if someone's there...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.30,0:02:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave-ho! Heave-ho! Heave-ho!...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.85,0:02:44.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It flew!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.31,0:02:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! The frog stopped. Corner it at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.81,0:02:54.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We ran ashore on something!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.23,0:02:56.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.71,0:03:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow, ow, ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.25,0:03:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go back! Go back! Turn 180 degrees!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.92,0:03:26.89,B1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(2000,2000)}"The Dashing Sea Train and\Nthe City of Water, Water Seven"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.68,0:03:29.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.93,0:03:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just turn around! Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.63,0:03:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.55,0:04:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Wh-What the hell is this lump of iron?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.84,0:04:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.64,0:04:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Something shaped like\Nthis can't travel on the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.64,0:04:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, frog! Run! What're you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.28,0:04:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahhh! It got run over!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.64,0:04:52.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ship was puffing out smoke!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.94,0:05:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pirates...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.49,0:05:07.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandma! Grandma! Pirates are here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.20,0:05:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Is that true, Chimney?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.29,0:05:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay then, bring the Transponder Snail to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.71,0:05:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.37,0:05:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a problem.\NSomeone came out of the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.54,0:05:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're gonna call for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.84,0:05:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is, Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.34,0:05:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Err... Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.63,0:05:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... What was it? I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.89,0:05:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she's drunk?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.35,0:05:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Paille, huh? It goes good with alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.78,0:05:44.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! This is good!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.24,0:05:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Chimney. This is our cat, Gonbe...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.86,0:05:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and Grandma Kokoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.32,0:05:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys aren't train robbers, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.24,0:05:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Luffy. I'm the man\Nwho'll be King of the Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.25,0:05:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Really?!\N--Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.63,0:06:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a funny guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.34,0:06:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Chimney, that thing is a steamship, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.96,0:06:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But with a shape like that,\Nit can't go on a voyage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.97,0:06:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've never seen something\Nlike that, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.84,0:06:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you look all over the world,\Nthis is the only place you can find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.10,0:06:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a sea train called the "Puffing Tom."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.89,0:06:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Puffing Tom?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.27,0:06:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It turns paddlewheels using a steam\Nengine and runs on the sea railway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.98,0:06:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Railway?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.36,0:06:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. It runs a little\Nbelow the surface of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.03,0:06:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The train travels the same route every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.41,0:06:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,taking passengers from one island to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.62,0:06:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It carries ships and the mail as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.04,0:06:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's right. There really is a railway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.04,0:06:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we ran ashore on that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.04,0:06:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! There's both\Na signal and a partition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.13,0:06:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's dangerous to come inside like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.71,0:06:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the signal should face the other way.\NOtherwise, how do we see it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.47,0:06:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's dangerous, that guy\Nwouldn't understand, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.72,0:06:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't nice to send him flying.\NWe were after him, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.64,0:07:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? "That guy"? Are you\Ntalking about Yokozuna?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.60,0:07:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep, that front crawl frog.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.36,0:07:06.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yokozuna wouldn't die from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.19,0:07:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the source of all our\Nheadaches at this shift station.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.36,0:07:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He loves strength contests and\Nalways tries to defeat the sea train.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.03,0:07:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll show up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.45,0:07:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Strength contests? Oh...\NThat's why he didn't run, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.45,0:07:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's sure got guts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.04,0:07:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break! We're having problems!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.21,0:07:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rail guard was broken many times, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.04,0:07:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every time he shows up, it causes\Nthe passengers a lot of trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.01,0:07:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.22,0:07:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then! I'm not gonna eat him!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.01,0:07:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna eat a fighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.97,0:07:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't have thought about\Neating a frog in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.52,0:07:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So where do you guys wanna go?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.14,0:07:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're gonna take the sea train from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.02,0:07:52.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The town of the Spring Queen, St. Poplar...\NThe gourmet town, Pucci...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.49,0:07:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Carnival town, San Faldo...\NThey're all fun places.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.20,0:08:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you work for the Government,\Nthere's a separate, special train.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.66,0:08:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gourmet town, Pucci?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.83,0:08:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.96,0:08:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the place the guys we met on the\Nuninhabited island were talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.59,0:08:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.43,0:08:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, we'll pick the gourmet town.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.26,0:08:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Obviously not!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.47,0:08:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since we've got our own ship,\Nwe won't take the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.06,0:08:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just follow the log.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.27,0:08:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...? Where is it pointing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.85,0:08:27.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,East of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.15,0:08:31.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Then it must be Water Seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.24,0:08:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The train you saw earlier came\Nfrom that island's Blue Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.20,0:08:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's called the "City of Water." It's a nice place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.37,0:08:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water Seven?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.45,0:08:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Above all, it's a city that made\Na name for itself with its shipyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.67,0:08:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their technology is No. 1 in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.71,0:08:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ships they build are the World\NGovernment's favorites! Isn't that amazing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.84,0:08:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... Then there's gotta be\Nsome amazing shipwrights, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.68,0:09:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not just "some"! It's a hangout\Nfor the world's best shipwrights!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.81,0:09:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Usopp!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.93,0:09:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.35,0:09:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! I've decided!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.64,0:09:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna go there and get a\Nshipwright to join our crew for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.77,0:09:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that right? Then hold on a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.73,0:09:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oof.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.44,0:09:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What's that about?\N--Beats me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.24,0:09:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then... Here's a simple map\Nof the island and a reference letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.91,0:09:27.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give this to a guy named Iceberg\Nand ask him to fix your ship good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.21,0:09:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water Seven is a big place. Don't get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.29,0:09:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Whoa!\N--Kokoro-san! You have a big heart!\NWhat a nice person you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.01,0:09:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna go back to Water Seven soon, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.51,0:09:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. If I see you guys again, I'll treat\Nyou to a drink at my favorite bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.94,0:09:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. I hope we'll see you guys again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.27,0:09:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll take about a week for the log to\Nbe stored in Water Seven. Take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.32,0:09:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, guys! Get ready to set sail!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.75,0:10:06.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Yeah!\N--Well then, we'll get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.79,0:10:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for all your help, Kokoro-san! Chimney!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.30,0:10:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.34,0:10:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out for the Government people!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.35,0:10:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yahoo! Let's go! To the city of meat! Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.27,0:10:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you even listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.16,0:10:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... What a nice wind!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.17,0:10:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We may be able to get to the city\Nof water sooner than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.96,0:10:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.71,0:11:01.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy, leave the shipwright search to me.\NI'll find an incredibly pretty woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.64,0:11:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you an idiot?! It's a\Nshipwright we're talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.60,0:11:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gotta be a big guy like\Na mountain! Five meters tall!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.10,0:11:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if he's too big, we don't know\Nif he could live okay on this ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.19,0:11:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that matters is that he's skilled, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.48,0:11:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, the question\Nis if we could find someone
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.53,0:11:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,crazy enough to want to be on a pirate ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.36,0:11:22.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking forward to it.\NWe're gonna have another new friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.70,0:11:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were lucky to stop at the station first,\Nsince they drew a map for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.12,0:11:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we go to the place on the map\Nand visit the Iceberg guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.37,0:11:32.58,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,"Around here" "Water Seven"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.83,0:11:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.58,0:11:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha! Too simple to figure out!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.21,0:11:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! This is like Luffy's drawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.71,0:11:39.92,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shipwright\N5 meters"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.71,0:11:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, we're gonna all look for a guy like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.67,0:11:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there was a guy like that, I'd run.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.55,0:11:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, me, too. If I had a boat,\NI'd escape to the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.05,0:11:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this guy seems to be related to octopuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.01,0:11:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He might follow me to the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.60,0:11:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you guys running on about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.44,0:11:53.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, guys, come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.15,0:11:56.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you some allowance for\Nthe week we're gonna stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.06,0:11:57.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?! Yaay! I'm first!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.61,0:11:59.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! That's generous!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.48,0:12:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Stand in line!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.95,0:12:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allowance! Allowance! Allowance!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.21,0:12:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Usopp?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.00,0:12:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This tinplate patchwork brings back\Nmemories of battles and adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.97,0:12:28.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm filled with deep emotions when I\Nthink that she will be repaired soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.22,0:12:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--I do understand that, but...\N--Hm...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.35,0:12:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...especially since we entered the Grand Line, our journey has taken quite a toll on the Merry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.02,0:12:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The deck squeaks and the leakage at\Nthe bottom of the ship is bad as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.65,0:12:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't do anything, both we\Nand the ship will be in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.15,0:12:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but we've got tons of money now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.45,0:12:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can have her repaired perfectly.\NWe can power her up, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.62,0:12:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Let's get more cannons!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.24,0:12:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, let's get a bronze statue on board, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.50,0:12:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, isn't that the one?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.33,0:12:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.79,0:13:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The island! We can see the island!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.47,0:13:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, guys! Paddle!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.55,0:13:08.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got enough wind.\NDon't make us waste our energy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.11,0:13:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How wonderful...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.86,0:13:22.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.37,0:13:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.25,0:13:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a huge fountain!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.34,0:13:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing! This is indeed an industrial city!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.17,0:13:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no surprise that this\Nplace would have a sea train.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.63,0:13:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow... This is a lot of water!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.47,0:13:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is that water springing out from?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.14,0:13:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How interesting... It looks like\Nthe water comes from the fountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.52,0:13:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,goes through the canals and falls into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.07,0:14:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do you wanna race on those water slides?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.36,0:14:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Race?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.16,0:14:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! There's no way I'm doing that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.62,0:14:19.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dream on, you idiot. You can't even swim.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.33,0:14:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.42,0:14:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly,\Nwhat do those numbers mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.21,0:14:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.01,0:14:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Don't know.\N--Are they walls? Or...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.84,0:14:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet those are the entrances\Nfor the five-meter shipwrights.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.84,0:14:34.68,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shipwright\N5 meters"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.72,0:14:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a bunch of them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.14,0:14:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one up front must be the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.89,0:14:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It says Blue Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.56,0:14:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder where the harbor is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.06,0:14:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be in the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.23,0:14:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hey, you guys!\N--Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.03,0:14:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not good for you pirates\Nto be openly sailing in the front!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.24,0:14:53.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go around to the backstreets over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.49,0:14:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.67,0:15:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, this is amazing! A city on the water?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.05,0:15:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! This place is cool! What a beautiful city!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.22,0:15:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the city is flooded.\NThe houses are submerged in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.23,0:15:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it. The city was designed\Nwith the base being submerged.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.69,0:15:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Huh?\N--Look at the foundation\Nunderneath the buildings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.45,0:15:32.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right! The pillars are built higher!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.86,0:15:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... That's why it's called\Nthe city of water, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.79,0:15:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hurry up and dock the ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.62,0:15:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.33,0:15:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, you guys!\NPirate ships shouldn't come in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.96,0:15:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you come here for?! To plunder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.96,0:15:50.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! We wanna get our ship repaired!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.63,0:15:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would people normally ask\Nif we're here to plunder?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.72,0:15:57.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, there's a cape ahead of here,\Nso anchor your ship there for now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.97,0:15:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.31,0:16:01.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.06,0:16:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.48,0:16:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be helped, right? We're pirates, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.11,0:16:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This area should be okay, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:12.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, what a dull place this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.78,0:16:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, then! Furl the sail!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.12,0:16:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.50,0:16:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing! I just pulled the rope!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.72,0:16:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Holy crap! The Going Merry\Nhas gotten this rickety?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.80,0:16:41.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, why aren't the people\Non this island scared of pirates?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.14,0:16:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because pirates are just\Nanother customer to their shipyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.64,0:16:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop talking and fix it already!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.40,0:16:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe because they have\Nbodyguards strong enough
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.28,0:16:52.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to deal with pirates who cause a ruckus?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.36,0:16:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They probably do...\Nconsidering the size of the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.57,0:16:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?! Hey, what're we gonna do? This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.20,0:17:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would it be bad? We're customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.75,0:17:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.91,0:17:04.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then! See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.66,0:17:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Luffy! Usopp!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.83,0:17:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys, come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.42,0:17:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.80,0:17:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To where?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.09,0:17:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, we'll take the reference\Nletter from Kokoro-san
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.18,0:17:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and go find the man named Iceberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.22,0:17:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll ask him to help us\Narrange the ship's repair.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.72,0:17:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We also have to find a place\Nwhere we can cash in our gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.85,0:17:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... All right, then! Anyway,\Nlet's go! To the city of water!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.69,0:17:33.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're forgetting the gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.74,0:17:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.74,0:17:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Zoro! Make sure you fix it good!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.41,0:17:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, Nami-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.50,0:17:47.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahh... I somehow missed\Nthe chance to go with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.04,0:17:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go out together later.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.17,0:17:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?! I wonder if they have a bookstore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.92,0:17:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.47,0:17:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we go to the\Nmoney-changing shop first?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.26,0:18:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Let's go to the shipyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.55,0:18:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't walk around the island\Nwith this much gold. I get nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.77,0:18:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even after changing it to money,\Nthe value is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.23,0:18:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true, but it being this big will\Nattract people's attention, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.15,0:18:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if we run into bad thieves?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.78,0:18:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the thieves!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.44,0:18:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's got a point. If we change it\Nto bills, we can all carry them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.82,0:18:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? Your remark had a sting to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.91,0:18:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like me carrying it is a problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.33,0:18:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. You might drop it somewhere or lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.79,0:18:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he would. It's Luffy we're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.75,0:18:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! You guys! Don't you trust me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.96,0:18:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Nope!\N--Ah... Ahh... Ahh... That really hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.46,0:18:39.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may not be able to recover from thi-- Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.14,0:18:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the only entrance to the city?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.76,0:18:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A rental bull shop?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.39,0:18:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.64,0:18:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do they rent out?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.64,0:18:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's "bull"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.06,0:18:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beats me. Bulldogs?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.07,0:18:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't be, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.02,0:18:57.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me! Please let us rent bulls!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.65,0:18:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask what they are first!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.86,0:19:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome! You wanna rent bulls, right?\NHow many are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.45,0:19:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.58,0:19:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of bulls would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.91,0:19:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There're three ranks.\N"Yagara," "Rabuka," and "King."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.41,0:19:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, for the three of you,\Ntwo Yagaras would probably do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.67,0:19:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Please roast them nice and tasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.59,0:19:16.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weird! That conversation is weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.84,0:19:19.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? You followed logs to get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.55,0:19:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Yep.\N--That's quite an achievement, you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.80,0:19:24.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you had no idea what bulls were, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.76,0:19:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Right.\N--Well, to make a long\Nstory short, those are bulls.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.47,0:19:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're Yagara bulls.\NThey're everywhere in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.52,0:19:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this area, there's a fish called\NYagara that swims with its head out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.52,0:19:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the city of water.\NThere're more canals than walkways.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.61,0:19:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So bulls are a means of transportation\Nnecessary to the residents here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.53,0:19:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same when you go\Nsightseeing on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.83,0:19:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That fish is pulling a boat?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.08,0:19:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than pulling, they're letting\Npeople ride on their back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.04,0:19:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's like horseback riding\Nor riding in a carriage on land...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.71,0:19:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oof.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.34,0:20:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see the fish pen there?\NWell, try and ride on it. It's comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.67,0:20:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be 2,000 Berries for two\Ntwo-passenger Yagara bulls.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.60,0:20:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, they're cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.80,0:20:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a fish that looks like a horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.77,0:20:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You jerk! What'd you do that for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.23,0:20:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? He must like you. Let's get him for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.86,0:20:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can he carry heavy stuff okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.82,0:20:30.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their power is incredible!\NYou can even use them for moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.16,0:20:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That bag, huh? What's inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.41,0:20:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.58,0:20:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're funny. Whatever it is, it'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.29,0:20:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--See?\N--Whoa! Give me some!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.26,0:20:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.34,0:20:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What an awfully honest old guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.09,0:20:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You too! Don't show it to others so lightly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.05,0:20:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? It wouldn't hurt, would it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.05,0:20:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My, my... What a surprise...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.43,0:20:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then... it'll be a million\NBerries for two Yagara bulls.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.85,0:20:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, the price went up, pops.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.81,0:20:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. It'll be five million Berries.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.94,0:21:00.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It went up even more!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.90,0:21:01.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.99,0:21:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez... We can't be too careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.24,0:21:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, 2,000 Berries.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.41,0:21:06.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.74,0:21:09.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, are there any\Nmoney-changing shops around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.49,0:21:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, there are, but with that amount of gold,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.08,0:21:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the shops around here probably\Nwouldn't have enough money.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.37,0:21:18.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should go to the downtown\Narea of the shipbuilding island.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.58,0:21:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The downtown area of the\Nshipbuilding island? Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.42,0:21:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's over there. Take this with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.97,0:21:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A map?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.89,0:21:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This'll be helpful! Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.14,0:21:32.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pops, is the shipyard there, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.27,0:21:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The world's No. 1 shipyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.77,0:21:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's perfect. Once we get the money,\Nwe can go to the shipyard right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.65,0:21:42.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We can finally have\Nthe Going Merry repaired!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.90,0:21:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we'll find a shipwright, too!\NI'm getting excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.24,0:21:48.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Well, then...\N--Shall we...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.61,0:21:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Go! Yagara!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.24,0:21:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for your business! Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.87,0:21:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dash to the shipyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.79,0:22:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.98,0:22:23.11,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,A piece of a dream that we started grasping
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.11,0:22:26.65,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Chasing after something constant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.65,0:22:32.24,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We send our aspirations sailing into the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.24,0:22:34.54,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when we're exhausted
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.54,0:22:37.71,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a compass that can\Nsearch for something constant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.71,0:22:43.13,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, do you think we can keep it forever?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.13,0:22:46.05,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,At the end of the dream\Nthat we will reach someday
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.05,0:22:49.09,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We want to be adults as we\Nare now as much as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.09,0:22:51.80,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We pray to this endless sky that we look up at
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.80,0:22:54.89,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Eternally... Eternally...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.89,0:22:57.68,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Wild fantasies from our childhood
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.68,0:23:00.52,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We trace unforgettable memories
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.52,0:23:06.19,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,And try to keep the embers\Nburning that still consume us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.19,0:23:09.11,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,To this familiar sunny sky
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.11,0:23:11.82,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Together we entrust our feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.82,0:23:14.41,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We go beyond the changing time
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.41,0:23:19.12,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Eternally... Eternally...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.46,0:23:27.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! This is fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.09,0:23:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's amazing that such a\Nconvenient creature exists!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.80,0:23:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't rock much. It's comfortable!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.76,0:23:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! The canals even go above the rooftops!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.72,0:23:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen such a huge town before!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.39,0:23:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. This is a town built around canals!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.72,0:23:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water Seven is getting me fired up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.31,0:23:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.98,0:23:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Adventure in the City on the Water!\NHead to the Mammoth Shipbuilding Plant"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.57,0:23:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
